File: Dumisani Mkhwanazi allegedly buried Palesa Madiba in a shallow grave in his mother’s backyard in Phiri, Soweto. JOHANNESBURG - A ruling in the Palesa Madiba murder case is expected on Friday. She went missing in 2013 after going to a friend's house for a sleepover. Her friend's relative, Dumisani Mkhwanazi, is accused of murdering the 21-year-old and burying her in a shallow grave. READ: Palesa Madiba murder trial postponed Her body was found two years later behind a back room of his family's home. Madiba was a final-year accounting student. The accused's failure to get legal representation has delayed the trial.